name: $collector
desc: Returns: Person who collected the specimen.

name: $quantity
desc: Returns: The quantity of specimen collected; for instance the volume of a blood sample, or the physical measurement of an anatomic pathology sample.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The quantity of specimen collected; for instance the volume of a blood sample, or the physical measurement of an anatomic pathology sample.

name: $method
desc: Returns: A coded value specifying the technique that is used to perform the procedure.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A coded value specifying the technique that is used to perform the procedure.

name: $bodySite
desc: Returns: Anatomical location from which the specimen was collected (if subject is a patient). This is the target site.  This element is not used for environmental specimens.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Anatomical location from which the specimen was collected (if subject is a patient). This is the target site.  This element is not used for environmental specimens.
